title: See 1
copy: Look around and notice everything that is green and blue in your environment.

title: See 2
copy: Pick out an object and focus on it as intensely as you can. When thoughts arise, let them go and refocus on the object.

title: See 3
copy: Lower your gaze, unfocus your eyes and pay attention to your entire visual field.

title: See 4
copy: Pick up an object and stare at it for 20 seconds. Who is looking at it? Who is looking at the thought "I am"?

title: See 5
copy: Close your eyes. Observe the patterns of light and dark on your eyelid.
